news.title: Vadodara: Builder cheated of Rs 1 crore by business partners in Waghodiya
news.para: The builder Prashant Trivedi lodged a complaint of cheating and forgery at Waghodiya police station on Monday after the partners Sunil Makhija and his brother Deepak Makhija did not return his money and sold off the properties promised to him to others.

news.title: China: Shares of Fantasia Holdings halve as trade resumes; misses bond payment
news.para: "Given the liquidity issue faced by the Group, there is no guarantee that the Group will be able to meet its financial obligations under its other financing documents," Fantasia Holdings said in the filing.

news.title: Gurugram civic body eyes revenue from building plan approvals
news.para: Additional commissioner Vaishali Sharma said on Tuesday that the aim of the survey is to prevent the construction of unauthorised buildings at the initial stages itself.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP sets up five teams to inspect sites for building violations
news.para: These teams, led by junior engineers, will inspect sites twice after the grant of OC — first within 10 days and the second within 45 days — and will report to the office of the district town planner.

news.title: Godrej & Boyce to retain 3,401 acres on business division
news.para: Of the 3,401 acres located in the eastern suburbs of Mumbai, roughly 1,750 acres of mangroves are part of the Soonabai Pirojsha Godrej Foundation.

news.title: Japan's Marubeni, Wadhwa Group in talks for real estate investment platform
news.para: The Wadhwa Group is eyeing redevelopment of old and dilapidated tenanted projects in India’s commercial capital as a growth opportunity for the company.

news.title: Sameer Gehlaut to quit as chairman of Indiabulls Real Estate
news.para: ​The change over will be effective February 1, 2022. For the last several months, Gehlaut has slowly been reducing his stake in the realty firm as Embassy Group is now taking charge of the entity to complete the process of merger with it.

news.title: Karnataka to cut property guidance value for Bengaluru areas in January 2022
news.para: Guidance value is the minimum selling price of a property fixed by the government depending on the locality and type of structure. While it is supposed to be revised every year, the government did not change the rates since January 2019 when they were hiked in the range of 5% to 25%.

news.title: MahaRERA conciliation forum told to wrap up cases in two months
news.para: An order to this effect was issued on Monday by MahaRERA secretary Vasant Prabhu as approved by chairperson Ajoy Mehta under Section 25 of the Real Estate Regulation and Development Act (RERA). “These directives were issued delays were noticed in most cases. A strict timeframe will have to be adhered to,” Prabhu said.

news.title: Office space leasing falls 4% to 25 million sq ft during Jan-Sep: CBRE
news.para: "Space take-up of 25 million square feet recorded in 2021 YTD (year-to-date), a marginal drop of 4 per cent year-on-year," CBRE said.

news.title: Delhi: NDMC halts construction activities at 54 sites, imposes fine
news.para: The corporation halted construction and demolition activities at sites of 54 private properties on Monday, where "violations of NGT norms were noticed," it said.

news.title: Kaisa Group says trying to solve liquidity issues, pleads for 'more time & patience'
news.para: Kaisa Group said in a statement on its official WeChat account that it was accelerating asset disposals in Shanghai and Shenzhen and using the proceeds for repayments, as well as accelerating its sales of existing properties.

news.title: Cash-strapped Evergrande raises $144 million before payment deadline
news.para: Evergrande sold a 5.7 percent stake totalling HK$1.12 billion ($144m) in HengTen Networks Group in three separate transactions from last Thursday, Hong Kong stock exchange filings showed.

news.title: Spanish property developer Neinor Homes in talks to buy Via Celere
news.para: Via Celere reported gross asset value (GAV) of 1.62 billion euros ($1.87 billion) in July, which would provide a significant boost to Neinor's market share and land bank. Neinor's GAV stood at 2.19 billion euros for the same reporting period.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate appoints KG Krishnamurthy as independent director
news.para: Krishnamurthy, who is former managing director & CEO of HDFC Property Ventures, will be designated as non-executive chairman of the company with effect from February 1, 2022.
